BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 1: Understanding Blood Pressure) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (What Blood Pressure Numbers Mean) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (Blood pressure is measured in two numbers:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (- Systolic \(top number\): Pressure when heart beats) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.2 Td (- Diastolic \(bottom number\): Pressure between beats) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 600.4 Td (Blood Pressure Categories) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584.4 Td (- Normal: Less than 120/80 mmHg) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (- Elevated: 120-129/less than 80 mmHg) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 556.4 Td (- Stage 1 Hypertension: 130-139/80-89 mmHg) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 542.4 Td (- Stage 2 Hypertension: 140+/90+ mmHg) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 528.4 Td (- Hypertensive Crisis: 180+/120+ \(seek emergency care\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 498.6 Td (Risk Factors You Can Control) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 480.6 Td (- Diet high in sodium and processed foods) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 466.6 Td (- Excess weight \(especially abdominal\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 452.6 Td (- Physical inactivity) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 438.6 Td (- Excessive alcohol consumption) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 424.6 Td (- Chronic stress) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 410.6 Td (- Smoking) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 396.6 Td (- Poor sleep and sleep apnea) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 366.8 Td (Complications of Uncontrolled Hypertension) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 348.8 Td (- Heart attack and heart failure) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 334.8 Td (- Stroke) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 320.8 Td (- Kidney disease and failure) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 306.8 Td (- Vision loss) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 292.8 Td (- Cognitive decline and dementia) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 278.8 Td (- Peripheral artery disease) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 249.0 Td (How to Measure Blood Pressure Correctly) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 231.0 Td (- Sit quietly for 5 minutes before measuring) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 217.0 Td (- Sit with back supported, feet flat on floor) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 203.0 Td (- Arm supported at heart level) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 189.0 Td (- Do not smoke, exercise, or drink caffeine 30 minutes before) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 175.0 Td (- Take 2-3 readings, 1 minute apart, and average them) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 161.0 Td (- Measure at the same time daily \(morning preferred\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 147.0 Td (- Use a validated upper-arm cuff monitor) Tj ET
endstream
