BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 3: The DASH Diet Guide) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 680.2 Td (DASH \(Dietary Approaches to Stop Hypertension\) is the most researched diet for blood) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 666.2 Td (pressure reduction. It can lower BP by 8-14 points.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 636.4 Td (DASH Diet Daily Servings) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 618.4 Td (- Grains: 6-8 servings \(whole grains preferred\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 604.4 Td (- Vegetables: 4-5 servings) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 590.4 Td (- Fruits: 4-5 servings) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 576.4 Td (- Low-fat dairy: 2-3 servings) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 562.4 Td (- Lean meats/fish: 6 oz or less) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 548.4 Td (- Nuts/seeds/legumes: 4-5 per week) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 534.4 Td (- Fats/oils: 2-3 servings \(healthy oils\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 520.4 Td (- Sweets: 5 or fewer per week) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 490.6 Td (Sodium Guidelines) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 472.6 Td (- Standard DASH: Less than 2,300mg sodium daily) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 458.6 Td (- Lower-sodium DASH: Less than 1,500mg daily \(greater BP reduction\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 430.8 Td (High-Sodium Foods to Avoid) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 414.8 Td (- Canned soups and vegetables \(choose low-sodium\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 400.8 Td (- Deli meats and processed meats) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 386.8 Td (- Frozen dinners and fast food) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 372.8 Td (- Condiments \(soy sauce, ketchup, salad dressings\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 358.8 Td (- Bread and rolls \(surprisingly high\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 344.8 Td (- Cheese \(especially processed\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 330.8 Td (- Pickles and olives) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 303.0 Td (Flavor Without Salt) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 287.0 Td (- Fresh herbs: basil, cilantro, parsley, dill) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 273.0 Td (- Spices: cumin, paprika, garlic powder, onion powder) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 259.0 Td (- Citrus: lemon, lime juice and zest) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 245.0 Td (- Vinegar: balsamic, apple cider, rice wine) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 231.0 Td (- Aromatics: garlic, ginger, onion) Tj ET
