110 0 obj
<< /Length 2873 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Frequently Asked Questions) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 676.2 Td (Q: How quickly can diet lower blood pressure?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 660.2 Td (The DASH diet can reduce BP within 2 weeks. Full benefits are typically seen at 4-6 weeks) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 646.2 Td (with consistent adherence.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 618.4 Td (Q: Can I stop my medication if BP improves?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (Never stop medication without doctor approval. Lifestyle changes may allow dose reduction) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (over time, but this must be medically supervised.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 560.6 Td (Q: Is coffee bad for blood pressure?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 544.6 Td (Caffeine can temporarily raise BP. If your readings are well-controlled, moderate coffee) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 530.6 Td (\(2-3 cups\) is generally acceptable. Monitor your response.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 502.8 Td (Q: How much sodium is too much?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 486.8 Td (Most health organizations recommend under 2,300mg daily. For greater BP reduction, aim for) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 472.8 Td (1,500mg. The average American consumes 3,400mg.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 445.0 Td (Q: Does stress really raise blood pressure?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 429.0 Td (Yes. Acute stress can spike BP 20+ points. Chronic stress keeps it elevated and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 415.0 Td (contributes to long-term hypertension through hormonal effects.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 387.2 Td (Q: What about potassium supplements?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 371.2 Td (Getting potassium from food is preferred. Supplements can be dangerous if you have kidney) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 357.2 Td (disease or take certain medications. Discuss with your doctor.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 329.4 Td (Q: Is white coat hypertension real?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 313.4 Td (Yes. Some people have elevated readings only in medical settings. Home monitoring provides) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 299.4 Td (more accurate data about your typical blood pressure.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 271.6 Td (Q: Can young people have high blood pressure?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 255.6 Td (Yes. Hypertension is increasing in younger adults due to obesity, poor diet, and sedentary) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 241.6 Td (lifestyles. Regular screening is important at any age.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 213.8 Td (Q: How accurate are home blood pressure monitors?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 197.8 Td (Validated upper-arm monitors are quite accurate. Bring yours to your doctor to compare) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 183.8 Td (readings. Wrist monitors are less reliable.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 156.0 Td (Q: Does alcohol affect blood pressure?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 140.0 Td (Yes. More than moderate drinking raises BP. Binge drinking can cause acute spikes.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 126.0 Td (Reducing alcohol is one of the most effective lifestyle changes.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
